## What this file does
[2–4 sentences. What problem does it solve? What layer of the application is it?
What would break if this file were deleted?]

## Exports and public interface
[List every exported function, class, type, or constant. For each:]
  name: ...
  signature: ... (full type signature if typed language)
  purpose: ... (one sentence)
  called_by: ... (which other files call this — use data from Pass 2)

## Internal structure
[Describe how the file is organized internally. Sections, classes, helper functions.
If there is a class, describe its constructor, key methods, and state it holds.
If there is a module pattern, describe the shape of the module.]

## How it connects to the task
[Be direct. "The task requires X. This file will need to Y because Z."]

## Exact insertion / modification points
[This is the most important section for the implementer.
Describe PRECISELY where the new code will go:]

  MODIFICATION 1:
  - location: after line containing `function getUserById` / inside class `UserService` / 
              at the end of the `routes` array / after the last import statement
  - what to add/change: [describe the change without writing the actual code]
  - why here: [why this location follows the existing pattern]

  MODIFICATION 2: ...

  NEW EXPORTS NEEDED: [list any new exports this file will need to expose]

## Conventions observed in this file
[Things specific to THIS file that the implementer must follow. Examples:
- "All async functions in this file use try/catch with a specific error shape"
- "All functions are documented with JSDoc before the function signature"
- "Parameters are validated at the top of the function before any logic"
Do NOT repeat global conventions already in Lens 1 unless this file deviates from them.]

## Gotchas and traps
[List 2–5 specific things that would trap an unfamiliar implementer.
Be concrete — reference actual variable names, patterns, or quirks in the file.]

BAD GOTCHA (useless): "Be careful with async code"
