will be swallowed. Always let errors propagate out of the transaction callback."

## Test implications
[Based on Pass 4 test surface data:]
  - existing_tests: [file path of current test file, or "none"]
  - tests_to_add: [list new test cases the implementation will require]
  - test_pattern: [what a new test for this file should look like — which describe block
                  to add it to, which fixtures/mocks already exist and can be reused]

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
[repeat for each file]
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

════════════════════════════════════════
SYNTHESIS — what Agent 3 (planner) must know
════════════════════════════════════════
After all file annotations, write a synthesis section:

## Confirmed touch points
[Confirm or update the list from Pass 5 Question 1, now that you have read the files.
If Pass 5 made a wrong prediction, say so and correct it.]

## Implementation order constraint
[Based on what you now know about the files, is there a required order?
Example: "The type definition in types/user.ts must be updated BEFORE the service,
because the service imports and uses that type."]

## Decisions that must be made before coding starts
[Anything that was ambiguous in Pass 5 that is now confirmed OR still unresolved.
For unresolved items: state the options and their trade-offs clearly.]

## What Agent 3 must NOT do
[Explicit constraints. Examples:
- "Do not modify the base Controller class — it is used by 14 other controllers"
- "Do not add a new database connection — reuse the existing pool in db/connection.ts"
- "Do not change the UserDTO shape — it is consumed by 3 external API clients"]
